data.text: @McMcdonde @LAURENCEJAMS please show evidence for such a correlation in European countries with high vaccination rates.

@LAURENCEJAMS I say this as someone who's been living in HK last few years. Staggering to see impact of omicron wave here vs in highly vaccinated populations like NZ, singapore and Queensland. Hospital situation in HK very scary. I wouldn't want to get sick for any reason there atm

@LAURENCEJAMS It's all about vaccination coverage in the elderly. It's abysmal. Care homes in particular the coverage is staggeringly low. And until a few weeks ago they were admitting every single case to hospital, even if asymptomatic. So hospitals got slammed before wave even really began
@McMcdonde @LAURENCEJAMS Indeed. Hadn't thought of that at all.
@LAURENCEJAMS During a normal flu season pre 2020 HK has this many weekly deaths but we'll see how it progresses.
@LAURENCEJAMS Hiding &/| bad reporting of actual data.
